Trim the @green beans{150%g} then chop into thirds. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(stalks and all). Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Chop the @diced British turkey breast{250%g} into 2cm chunks.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} over a medium-high heat. When hot, add the turkey chunks and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir and cook until coloured, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Next add the green beans and cook until they begin to soften, ~{3%minutes}. Add the @mild curry powder{1%tsp}, stir and cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When the curry has a few minutes left, cook the @brown rice & quinoa{1%pack} according to pack instructions. Share between your #bowls{} and stir through a little lime zest.

Once the curry is ready, stir in half the coriander, the remaining lime zest and add a good squeeze of lime juice. Season to taste with more salt and pepper if needed. Serve on top of the rice and finish with a sprinkling of remaining coriander and the @cashew pieces{25%g}. Enjoy!

> When the curry is ready, stir in the remaining lime zest and add a good squeeze of lime juice.
> Season to taste with salt and pepper.
> Serve on top of the rice and finish with a sprinkle of coriander and the cashew nuts.